In current practice, '''climacteric''' is most often a synonym for female [[menopause]]. In Princeton University's online Wordnet database, climacteric is listed as: <ref name="titleWordNet Search - 3.0">{{cite web |url=http://wordnet.princeton.edu/perl/webwn |title=WordNet Search - 3.0 |accessdate=2007-12-17 |format= |work=}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>

* (n) climacteric (a period in a man's life corresponding to menopause)
 
*  (n) menopause, climacteric, change of life (the time in a woman's life in which the menstrual cycle ends) 

The term is used for both genders by [http://www.imsociety.org The International Menopause Society], which defines itself as "The society for the study of all aspects of the climacteric in men and women."

